The paper deals with source coding and distortion measures, which are topics typically studied in information theory (cs.IT). The concept of side information is also relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the penalty for deviating from certain configurations, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
